MODIFICATIONS TO JTC REPAIR LAB FLUTTER APP
============================================

Apply the following changes to the existing JTC Repair Lab Flutter app:

─────────────────────────────────────────────
CHANGE 1: BILL / RECEIPT UPGRADES
─────────────────────────────────────────────

1a. URDU HEADER ON BILL
- At the very top of the printed/preview bill, show the shop name in Urdu:
  جُنید ٹیلی کام ریپیئرنگ لیب
- Below it show contact info:
  Usman: 0345-7599995
  Saad:  0345-7701965
- At the bottom of the bill show this address line in Urdu:
  نزد ڈھول سکندر، محلہ گڑھ، چنیوٹ
- Use a font that supports Urdu/Arabic script. Use the 'google_fonts' package 
  with 'NotoNastaliqUrdu' or embed a .ttf Urdu font asset in the app.
- Urdu text must be Right-to-Left (RTL) aligned.

1b. BILL PREVIEW SCREEN
- Before printing, show a full scrollable preview of the bill inside the app.
- The preview must look exactly like the printed output (same layout, same fonts).
- Use a white card with a subtle shadow to simulate a paper receipt.
- Add a "Print" button and a "Share" button at the bottom of the preview screen.

1c. SHAREABLE BILL (IMAGE + PDF)
- Add two share options on the bill preview screen:
  OPTION A — Share as Image (PNG):
    - Capture the bill preview widget using RepaintBoundary + RenderRepaintBoundary.
    - Save as PNG to temporary directory using path_provider.
    - Open native share sheet using the 'share_plus' package.
  OPTION B — Share as PDF:
    - Generate a PDF of the bill using the 'pdf' package (pub.dev package: pdf ^3.10.x).
    - Use the 'printing' package (^5.12.x) for both PDF preview and share/print.
    - The PDF must contain all bill fields including Urdu text (embed Urdu font in PDF).
    - Share via native share sheet or open print dialog.
- Add these packages to pubspec.yaml:
    share_plus: ^7.2.2
    pdf: ^3.10.8
    printing: ^5.12.0

─────────────────────────────────────────────
CHANGE 2: IN-APP NOTIFICATIONS (LOCAL PUSH)
─────────────────────────────────────────────

- Add the 'flutter_local_notifications' package (^17.x.x) to pubspec.yaml.
- Initialize notifications in main.dart with an Android notification channel 
  named "JTC Lab Alerts" with HIGH importance.
- Show a local notification popup in these events:
  a) New repair job saved → "New Job Added ✅" with customer name + device model in body.
  b) Job marked as Done → "Repair Complete 🎉" with customer name + device model.
  c) Issue reported on a job → "Issue Found ⚠️" with the issue note in body.
  d) Borrow item added → "Part Borrowed 📦" with part name + shop name.
- Notifications must appear even when the app is in the foreground (use 
  onDidReceiveNotificationResponse for foreground handling).
- Add POST_NOTIFICATIONS permission to AndroidManifest.xml for Android 13+.
- Request notification permission at app startup using permission_handler.

─────────────────────────────────────────────
CHANGE 3: iOS 26 / GLASSMORPHISM UI OVERHAUL
─────────────────────────────────────────────

- Redesign the entire app UI with a modern Glassmorphism style inspired by iOS 26.
- Keep the white base background but add frosted-glass cards throughout.

Glass card effect (apply to ALL cards/containers):
  - Use BackdropFilter with ImageFilter.blur(sigmaX: 12, sigmaY: 12).
  - Container decoration:
      color: Colors.white.withOpacity(0.55)
      borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(24)
      border: Border.all(color: Colors.white.withOpacity(0.6), width: 1.2)
      boxShadow: [
        BoxShadow(
          color: Colors.blue.withOpacity(0.08),
          blurRadius: 24, spreadRadius: 2,
        )
      ]
  - Wrap in ClipRRect with matching borderRadius for blur to clip correctly.

Background:
  - Use a full-screen gradient background on every screen:
      LinearGradient(
        colors: [Color(0xFFE8F0FF), Color(0xFFF5F0FF), Color(0xFFE0F7FF)],
        begin: Alignment.topLeft, end: Alignment.bottomRight,
      )
  - Add 2–3 large soft blurred colored circles (blobs) positioned in corners 
    of the screen as decorative background elements (use positioned containers 
    with blur, opacity 0.25, colors: blue, purple, teal).

Typography & spacing:
  - All font sizes increase by 1pt for readability.
  - Use more generous padding (20px inside cards instead of 14px).
  - Section labels use uppercase letter-spacing 1.2.

AppBar:
  - Transparent AppBar with blur effect (use SliverAppBar or custom).
  - No hard background color — glass effect behind title.

Buttons:
  - Primary buttons: gradient background (Blue #1A73E8 → #0D47A1), 
    borderRadius 20, slight shadow.
  - Secondary buttons: glass style (white with opacity + border).

Chips (issue tags, filters):
  - Selected: solid gradient blue.
  - Unselected: glass style with blue border.

Bottom sheets:
  - Glass background with blur, rounded top corners radius 28.

